The paper proposes a coding scheme to address a specific problem in 3D vertical flash memory. This involves incorporating side information during the encoding stage, which is closely related to the problem of coding in a memory with defective cells. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with issues related to memory architecture and control, which could fall under the Architecture (cs.AR), Data Structures (cs.DS), and Embedded Systems (cs.ET) sub-categories. Finally, the proposed scheme involves intentional interference between cells, which could also be relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
